{{Italic title|force=yes}}
'''''Research in Social Movements, Conflicts and Change''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[Monographic series|book series]] that covers [[sociology|sociological]] research on [[social conflict]], [[social movements]], [[collective behavior]], and [[social change]]. The journal also publishes [[book review|reviews of books]] on these topics. It was established in 1977 and is published by [[Emerald Group Publishing]].

The journal's founding [[editor-in-chief]] was [[Louis Kriesberg]] ([[Syracuse University]]). Since 2010, the editor is [[Patrick G. Coy]] ([[Kent State University]]).

