{{refimprove|date=August 2017}} {{Infobox settlement |name = Srowolan |official_name = Dusun Srowolan |settlement_type = [[Administrative village|Village]] |image_skyline = Pasar Perjuangan Srowolan.jpg |imagesize = |image_caption = A view of the Pasar Perjuangan market which acts as the village square and common meeting place. It is built on land owned by the Sultan of Yogyakarta. |image_flag = |image_seal = |image_shield = |image_map = |mapsize = |map_caption = |pushpin_map = Indonesia#Yogyakarta |pushpin_map_caption = Location of Srowolan in Indonesia |timezone = [[Time in Indonesia|WIB]] |utc_offset = +7 |footnotes = }}<!-- Infobox ends -->
'''Srowolan''' is a [[Administrative village|village]] in the [[Special Region of Yogyakarta]]. It is situated in the southern foothills of [[Mount Merapi]] exactly {{convert|15|km|abbr=on}} south of the peak {{convert|15|km|abbr=on}} north of the ''[[Kraton Ngayogyakarta Hadiningrat]]''.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://gudeg.net/direktori/1816/desa-wisata-srowolan-yogyakarta.html | title=Desa Wisata Srowolan | publisher=GudegNet | accessdate=August 3, 2017}}</ref>
Some of the main attractions of this village include ''Banyusumilir'', an outbound business owned by a local resident, [[salak]] orchards, and ''Pasar Perjuangan'' market. The market, established in 1921 by the Sultan, has not been active for over thirty years.
